e country should equal the spread of Ujamaa socialism. When this did not happen, the verdict of failure was proclaimed on Swahili, which did not prevent the language from becoming one of the most widely used and dynamic languages on the continent.This book is a thoroughly revised version of the 1999 edition, which was welcomed at the time as a classic. It now extends the period of coverage to 2012 and includes an entirely new chapter on current developments, making this updated edition an essential read for students and scholars in language, linguistics and African Studies."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aIdeologyxTanzania. 0aIdeologyzTanzania. 0aIdeology. 0aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / GeneralxTanzania. 0aLanguage planningxTanzania. 0aLanguage planningzTanzania. 0aLanguage planning. 0aLanguage policyxTanzania. 0aLanguage policyzTanzania. 0aLanguage policy. 0aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Cultural Policy. 0aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural. 0aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture. 0aSwahili languagexPolitical aspectsxTanzania. 0aSwahili languagexPolitical aspectszTanzania. 0aSwahili languagexPolitical aspects. 4aLanguage & Linguistics. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311078045140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978074867581440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748675814423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780748675814/original  a978-3-11-078045-1  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11S